body:
General idea:

```
parameter ct = "ABC";
(* cell_type = ct *)
_dummy_ my_cell(... ports ...);
```

would be converted (by the verilog frontend) to:

```
ABC my_cell(... ports ...);
```

Likewise,

```
parameter cn = "ABC";
(* cell_name = cn *)
my_submod _dummy_(... ports ...);
```

would be converted to:

```
my_submod ABC(... ports ...);
```

